postcontent:
I have an authentic civil war cavalry officer's saber I am considering trading. I am unsure I want to turn loose of it, but will consider for the right trade. It is of a fairly rare maker mark. "Henry Boker" of Solingen Germany who did make swords for both the north and the south during the civil war. Herman Boker his brother lived in the north eastern US and imported his brother's swords in support of the civil war. Boker Cutlery is still around today. There are some condition issues with the sword, but damn, it's a battle saber and had a rough life ya think? ;) These are prized in any condition. I have seen some in much better condition, and I have seen many in much worse than relic condition. This one is in-between.
